and away it goes.

00:33:38.070 --> 00:33:42.280
It logs how long it took to image,
when it re-imaged its last time.

00:33:42.370 --> 00:33:45.140
And we run a whole pile of
user interactions which I don't

00:33:45.140 --> 00:33:46.400
have time to talk about.

00:33:46.480 --> 00:33:49.470
So it stores user data,
how many pages they printed,

00:33:49.670 --> 00:33:52.120
what applications they launched,
what they did,

00:33:52.150 --> 00:33:53.440
and we're looking at expanding that.

00:33:53.450 --> 00:33:56.220
So we get some really serious granular
data of what students are doing.

00:33:56.500 --> 00:33:58.130
And this is all in a SQL database.

00:33:58.140 --> 00:34:01.310
You can write, and we will be writing,
a whole pile of XML code to suck

00:34:01.320 --> 00:34:04.210
it out and give you live reports
of what your machines are doing.

00:34:04.390 --> 00:34:06.840
And remember,
you haven't left your desk yet.

